reg_pit.title: Managed Forest Land and Cut Timber Values Regulation

change.changenote: Section 1 definition of "sawlog" BEFORE amended by BC Reg 287/2009, effective November 30, 2009.

definition.def: has the same meaning as in the Scaling Regulation, B.C. Reg. 446/94, under the Schedule of Interior Timber Grades — All Species, and includes timber graded as Dead and Dry Sawlog, Grade Code 3;

change.changenote: Section 1 definitions of "grade", "sawlog" and "special forest product" BEFORE amended by BC Reg 390/2012, effective December 7, 2012.

paragraph.paragraphtext: with respect to a coastal area, the quality of cut timber as defined in the Schedule of Coast Timber Grades under the Scaling Regulation, B.C. Reg. 446/94, and
with respect to an interior area, the quality of cut timber as defined in the Schedule of Interior Timber Grades — All Species under the Scaling Regulation, B.C. Reg. 446/94;

definition.def: has the same meaning as in the Scaling Regulation, B.C. Reg. 446/94, under the Schedule of Interior Timber Grades — All Species;
means a product of cut timber as defined in the Special Forest Products Regulation, B.C. Reg. 241/2003, made under the Forest Act;

change.changenote: Section 1 (1) definition of "valuation area" BEFORE amended by BC Reg 265/2015, effective December 23, 2015.

bcl:paragraph.bcl:text: with respect to a coastal area, the valuation areas numbered 1 to 4 on the map in Schedule A, and
with respect to an interior area, the valuation areas numbered 5 to 9 on the map in Schedule A.

change.changenote: Section 5 (3) BEFORE amended by BC Reg 287/2009, effective November 30, 2009.

subsection.subsectiontext: The value of Grade Codes 4 and 5 in an interior area must be set at 50% of the sawlog value, and Grade Code 6 must be given a value of $1.00 per cubic metre or such value as is determined from time to time by the assessment authority.

change.changenote: Section 5 (2) BEFORE amended by BC Reg 318/2016, effective December 19, 2016.

bcl:subsection.bcl:text: The value of special forest products shall be determined using the rates shown in the column headed "ungraded" for species and grade in Schedule C, or the column headed "sawlog" in Schedule D as appropriate.
